An LRU cache needs to:
- Support get(key) operation that returns the value and marks it as recently used
- Support put(key, value) operation that adds/updates a key-value pair
- When capacity is reached, evict the least recently used item
- Both operations should be O(1)

The classic approach is to use:
1. A HashMap (JavaScript Map) for O(1) lookup
2. A Doubly Linked List to maintain the order of access (recently used at head, least recently used at tail)

When we get or put a key, we move it to the head (most recently used).
When we need to evict, we remove from the tail.

